-- Turkey Stocks Movers: Petkim Petrokimya, Turcas Petrol
-- B y   A y d a n   E k s i n
-- 2011-12-28T16:15:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-28/turkey-stocks-movers-petkim-petrokimya-turcas-petrol.html
Turkey’s benchmark  ISE National 100
Index (XU100)  fell 1.9 percent to 51,553.20 at the 5:30 p.m. close in
Istanbul, declining the most in two weeks.  The following stocks were active on the Turkish stock
market today. Stock symbols are in parentheses.  Turcas Petrol AS (TRCAS)  , a Turkish fuel retailer,
jumped 2.4 percent to 2.15 liras, in the biggest advance since
Dec. 2. Turcas agreed to sell its 25 percent stake in Socar &
Turcas Enerji AS to the State Oil Co. of Azerbaijan, known as
Socar, for $44 million,  Petkim Petrokimya Holding AS (PETKM) , Turkey’s
biggest chemicals maker controlled by Socar & Turcas Enerji,
said. Turcas also signed an accord to buy 18.5 percent of Socar
& Turcas Rafineri AS from Socar & Turcas Enerji for 9.25 million
liras, Petkim said in a statement to the bourse today. Turcas
aims to focus on refining and fuel retailing, the company said
Dec. 19.  Petkim (PETKM TI) fell 0.5 percent to 1.99 liras.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Aydan Eksin in Istanbul at 
